# CODEOWNERS — operator review required for paths listed below.
#
# Combined with the ``main`` ruleset (which requires PRs for direct pushes),
# this is the gate that keeps the BASELINES_COMMIT_TOKEN-bypass bot from
# escaping its data/baselines/* sandbox: any PR that would let the
# nightly-data-baseline job stage non-baseline paths requires operator
# approval before it can land.
#
# Pattern order matters — later entries override earlier ones.

# Default: anyone can review. Specific gated paths below.
*  @chipi

# Baseline workflow + scripts — gate against tampering that would expand
# the bot's write surface beyond data/baselines/*.
.github/workflows/nightly-data-baseline.yml  @chipi
scripts/baselines/**                          @chipi

# CODEOWNERS itself — don't let it edit itself away.
.github/CODEOWNERS                            @chipi
